name: Texans
summary: The Houston Texans, currently 1-4, have a busy week ahead. With just three weeks remaining in the season, the team announced roster transactions. In a preview of their upcoming game, the Tennessee Titans will conclude their season at home against the Texans. Despite their struggles, the Texans cling to playoff hopes. A recent article breaks down the possible scenarios for them to make the playoffs through Week 17. Rookie Brian Thomas Jr. has been a standout player for the Jacksonville Jaguars, scoring in their recent victory over the Titans. Additionally, the Texans have revealed that they will be wearing Oilers uniforms during their home game against the Titans. Diontae Johnson, a new wide receiver for the Texans, expressed his excitement for a "fresh start" in Houston. Various media outlets have analyzed the Texans' playoff matchups and potential opponents. Despite their low standing, the Texans still have opportunities to secure a playoff berth. An article by Texans Wire explains why Week 18 is not entirely meaningless for the team.

name: Trey Lance
summary: The Dallas Cowboys announced that Trey Lance will start as quarterback in their final regular season game against the Washington Commanders. Lance expressed confidence in his ability to lead the team as a starter and reflected on his growth as a player. The Cowboys' decision to start Lance was reportedly based on a desire to give him "significant snaps" and gain a better understanding of his potential. Lance himself expressed his desire for more opportunities to showcase his skills in the future. Despite being a third-string quarterback, Lance's performance in his first start was highly anticipated, with some speculating that his future with the Cowboys could be determined by his play.

name: Tanner McKee
summary: Tanner McKee, the quarterback for the Philadelphia Eagles, made his NFL debut and impressed with a strong performance. McKee led a 19-yard gain with a pass to Jahan Dotson. While the Eagles missed one goal against the Giants, analysts believe this may not affect their playoff chances. Several teams, including the Indianapolis Colts and Las Vegas Raiders, are reportedly interested in acquiring McKee in a trade. Despite not having played in any regular season games before this season, McKee made NFL history with his performance. Notably, A.J. Brown threw McKee's first touchdown pass ball into the crowd, which was later returned to McKee by an Eagles fan. The team captured the heartwarming moment and Brown signed a jersey for the fan who returned the ball.
